<subSubSection lastPageId="66" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,1193,2010]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1301,1326]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Description.</emphasis>
<collectionCode box="[355,439,1302,1326]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">BODY</collectionCode>
: Length 
<quantity box="[543,651,1302,1326]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.20 mm</quantity>
; brown with elytra and appendages orange-brown; setae over body decumbent, longest on abdomen. 
<emphasis box="[549,609,1337,1362]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Head</emphasis>
: surface smooth, shining, lightly microreticulate, punctures indistinct. Antennomeres III–VI longer than wide, VII as long as wide, VIII–X transverse, VIII about two-thirds width of IX (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1409,1434]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1849,1871]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,278,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[156,1431,265,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 28. Brachygluta seri Chandler (Mexico, Baja California, Isla San Esteban, holotype). A: Abdomen, dorsal view. B: Abdomen, caudal view. C: Right antenna. D: Left metatibia, anterior view. E: Aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288084/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,245,1410,1434]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Setose area of median vertexal fovea as large as those of lateral foveae. 
<emphasis box="[1127,1238,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Pronotum</emphasis>
: surface shining, lightly microreticulate, punctures indistinct. Setose area of median antebasal fovea about two-thirds width of lateral antebasal foveae. 
<emphasis box="[358,428,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Elytra</emphasis>
: microreticulate, surface granulate, punctures indistinct, discal stria faint, extending to about three-fourths of elytral length. 
<emphasis box="[563,669,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Abdomen</emphasis>
: disc with small, distinct punctures, basal two tergites opaque due to distinct microreticulation, apical tergites more shining; basal striae of tergite 
<number box="[1010,1024,1554,1578]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
short/indistinct, separated at base by about three-fifths tergite width; setose comb at base between basal striae sparse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,1193,2010]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
MALE: Antennae and trochanters lacking modifications, simple. Metaventrite with rounded-triangular area extending anteriorly from metacoxae to anterior portion of disc, area with dense long setae, metasternal disc laterally with setae distinct but becoming sparser. Tergite 
<number box="[820,834,1698,1722]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
distinctly microreticulate across disc, apical margin slightly concave, with broad impression in basal third of disc (
<figureCitation box="[892,979,1733,1758]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1849,1871]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,278,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[156,1431,265,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 28. Brachygluta seri Chandler (Mexico, Baja California, Isla San Esteban, holotype). A: Abdomen, dorsal view. B: Abdomen, caudal view. C: Right antenna. D: Left metatibia, anterior view. E: Aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288084/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[949,979,1734,1758]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
A); in lateral view tergite apex slightly protruding out over tergite 
<number box="[453,470,1770,1794]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
; tergite 
<number box="[559,573,1770,1794]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
only slightly longer than tergite 
<number box="[939,956,1770,1794]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
. Tergite 
<number box="[1052,1066,1770,1794]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
with semicircular basal carina in median fourth just covered by apex of tergite 
<number box="[665,680,1806,1830]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
; tergites 
<number box="[784,821,1806,1830]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3</number>
slightly and broadly impressed at middle across width (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1849,1871]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,278,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[156,1431,265,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 28. Brachygluta seri Chandler (Mexico, Baja California, Isla San Esteban, holotype). A: Abdomen, dorsal view. B: Abdomen, caudal view. C: Right antenna. D: Left metatibia, anterior view. E: Aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288084/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,246,1842,1866]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Ventrites broadly rounded. Metatibiae thin, narrow at base, gradually widened to near apex, mesal margin of apical fifth with brush present (
<figureCitation box="[642,728,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1849,1871]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,278,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[156,1431,265,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 28. Brachygluta seri Chandler (Mexico, Baja California, Isla San Esteban, holotype). A: Abdomen, dorsal view. B: Abdomen, caudal view. C: Right antenna. D: Left metatibia, anterior view. E: Aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288084/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[698,728,1878,1902]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Aedeagus 
<quantity box="[894,997,1878,1902]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long; dorsal plate rounded triangular, margins evenly converging to bluntly rounded point; parameres rounded at apex, three thick setae on lateral margin at angle of distinct preapical constriction; thickened hyaline seta on mesal margin, longer than preapical setae, thickened to middle, with acute apex; internal sac with four curved large spines (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1137,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1849,1871]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,278,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@66.[156,1431,265,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 28. Brachygluta seri Chandler (Mexico, Baja California, Isla San Esteban, holotype). A: Abdomen, dorsal view. B: Abdomen, caudal view. C: Right antenna. D: Left metatibia, anterior view. E: Aedeagus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288084/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[1107,1137,1986,2010]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[199,895,151,213]" box="[199,443,151,176]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">FEMALE: Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[199,895,151,213]" box="[199,895,188,213]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
